Sounds good. You may want to consider a special routine like:
ASTNode.resolveDeprecatedAnnotations that per its javadoc:
/** * Figures if @Deprecated annotation is specified, do not resolve entire annotations. */
Also see org.eclipse.jdt.internal.compiler.lookup.AnnotationBinding.addStandardAnnotations(AnnotationBinding[], long, LookupEnvironment)
ran out of time for M3.

With the existing analysis the fix seems to be easier than I thought:
We already have the infrastructure to defer bound checks, and some checks for member value pairs already piggy-back on that mechanism.
Only the scope of this deferring needs to be fine tuned:
- As per bug 434630 we need to keep deferring as long as the *CUScope* is connecting hierarchies
- As per this bug individual ClassScopes need to signal deferring, too, because we may enter through side doors like ClassScope.connectTypeHierarchyWithoutMembers() line: 1146 ClassScope.detectHierarchyCycle(TypeBinding, TypeReference) line: 1173 SingleTypeReference.getTypeBinding(Scope) line: 61 in addition to folks coming through the front door at CompilationUnitScope.connectTypeHierarchy()
Hence, the best fix seems to be to just move the triggers for setting/resetting CUScope.connectingHierarchy into the corresponding methods in ClassScope, while in fact keeping the flag in CUScope. This should get us the best of both worlds.
See https://git.eclipse.org/r/#/c/36997/
